	Ø Every file has 3 type permissions

	1. User level
	2. Group level
	3. Other level

Permission types
==============
R -> read permission 
W -> write permission 
X - > executable permission 


	1. Chmod:- change permissions (read, write and execute)
	2. Chown:- change ownership ( user and group)


R -> 4
W -> 2
X -> 1

	Ø These numbers are important for numeric mode

Chmod
======

	Ø There are two ways to change the file names using chmod

	1. Symbolic mode (easy for beginners)

Syntax :-  chmod who operator permission file

Chmod -> command
Who -> user or group or other
Operators-> +, -
Permission:- r, w,x
file:- file name
